cSctpMIB.name: cSctpMIB

revisions.description: MIB module developed for the SIGTRAN IETF group. Based on SCTP, RFC2960 - Added textual convention for InetPortNumber Imported TEXTUAL-CONVENTION from FROM SNMPv2-TC and locally defined InetPortNumber. -- Commented out some compliance statements that did not compile. This MIB is based on the following IETF document. draft-ietf-sigtran-sctp-mib-04.txt

cSctpMIB.contactinfo: Maria-Carmen Belinchon-Vergara Jose-Javier Pastor-Balbas Postal: Ericsson Espana S. A. Ombu street 1, 4th floor 28045 Madrid Spain Phones: +34 91 339 3535 +34 91 339 3819 Emails: Maria.C.Belinchon@ericsson.com J.Javier.Pastor@ericsson.com cs-sctp@cisco.com
cSctpMIB.description: The MIB module for managing SCTP protocol (RFC 2960).

cSctpRtoAlgorithm.name: cSctpRtoAlgorithm
cSctpRtoAlgorithm.description: The algorithm used to determine the timeout value (T3-rtx) used for re-transmitting unacknowledged chunks.

cSctpRtoMin.name: cSctpRtoMin
cSctpRtoMin.description: The minimum value permitted by a SCTP implementation for the retransmission timeout, measured in milliseconds. More refined semantics for objects of this type depend upon the algorithm used to determine the retransmission timeout. Minimum recommended value is 1000 milliseconds. Some telephony applications could require less than 1 second, see [SIGAS] for further information.

cSctpRtoMax.name: cSctpRtoMax
cSctpRtoMax.description: The maximum value permitted by a SCTP implementation for the retransmission timeout, measured in milliseconds. More refined semantics for objects of this type depend upon the algorithm used to determine the retransmission timeout. Recommended value is 60000 milliseconds.

cSctpRtoInitial.name: cSctpRtoInitial
cSctpRtoInitial.description: Initial value for the Retransmission timer. Recommended value is 3000 milliseconds.

cSctpMaxAssoc.name: cSctpMaxAssoc
cSctpMaxAssoc.description: The limit on the total number of SCTP associations the entitycan support. In entities where the maximum number of associations is dynamic, this object should contain the value -1.

cSctpValCookieLife.name: cSctpValCookieLife
cSctpValCookieLife.description: Valid cookie life in the 4-way start-up handshake procedure. Recommended value: 60000 milliseconds.

cSctpMaxInitRetr.name: cSctpMaxInitRetr
cSctpMaxInitRetr.description: The maximum number of retransmissions at the start-up phase (INIT and COOKIE ECHO chunks). Recommended value: 8 attempts.

cSctpCurrEstab.name: cSctpCurrEstab
cSctpCurrEstab.description: The number of SCTP associations for which the current state is either ESTABLISHED, SHUTDOWN-RECEIVED or SHUTDOWN-PENDING.

cSctpActiveEstabs.name: cSctpActiveEstabs
cSctpActiveEstabs.description: The number of times that SCTP associations have made a direct transition to the ESTABLISHED state from the COOKIE-ECHOED state: COOKIE-ECHOED -> ESTABLISHED. The upper layer has initiated the association attempt.

cSctpPassiveEstabs.name: cSctpPassiveEstabs
cSctpPassiveEstabs.description: The number of times that SCTP associations have made a direct transition to the ESTABLISHED state from the CLOSED state: CLOSED -> ESTABLISHED. The remote endpoint has initiated the association attempt.

cSctpAborteds.name: cSctpAborteds
cSctpAborteds.description: The number of times that SCTP associations have made a direct transition to the CLOSED state from any state using the primitive 'ABORT': AnyState --Abort--> CLOSED. Ungraceful termination of the association.

cSctpShutdowns.name: cSctpShutdowns
cSctpShutdowns.description: The number of times that SCTP associations have made a direct transition to the CLOSED state from either the SHUTDOWN-SENT state or the SHUTDOWN-ACK-SENT state. Graceful termination of the association.

cSctpStatOutOfBlues.name: cSctpStatOutOfBlues
cSctpStatOutOfBlues.description: Number of out of the blue packets (SCTP packet correctly formed -right checksum- but the receiver is not able to identify the association to which this packet belongs) received by the host.

cSctpStatChecksumErrors.name: cSctpStatChecksumErrors
cSctpStatChecksumErrors.description: Number of SCTP packets received from the peers with an invalid checksum.

cSctpStatSentCtrlChunks.name: cSctpStatSentCtrlChunks
cSctpStatSentCtrlChunks.description: Number of SCTP control chunks sent to the peers (no retransmissions included).

cSctpStatSentOrderChunks.name: cSctpStatSentOrderChunks
cSctpStatSentOrderChunks.description: Number of SCTP ordered data chunks sent to the peers (no retransmissions included).

cSctpStatSentUnorderChunks.name: cSctpStatSentUnorderChunks
cSctpStatSentUnorderChunks.description: Number of SCTP unordered chunks (data chunks in which the U bit is set to 1) sent to the peers (no retransmissions included).

cSctpStatRecCtrlChunks.name: cSctpStatRecCtrlChunks
cSctpStatRecCtrlChunks.description: Number of SCTP control chunks received from the peers (no duplicated included).

cSctpStatRecOrderChunks.name: cSctpStatRecOrderChunks
cSctpStatRecOrderChunks.description: Number of SCTP ordered data chunks received from the peers (no duplicated included).

cSctpStatRecUnorderChunks.name: cSctpStatRecUnorderChunks
cSctpStatRecUnorderChunks.description: Number of SCTP unordered chunks (data chunks in which the U bit is set to 1) received from the peers (no duplicated included).

cSctpStatFragmentedUsrMessages.name: cSctpStatFragmentedUsrMessages
cSctpStatFragmentedUsrMessages.description: Number of user messages that have to be fragmented because of the MTU.

cSctpStatSentSCTPPacks.name: cSctpStatSentSCTPPacks
cSctpStatSentSCTPPacks.description: Number of SCTP packets received from the peers.

cSctpStatRecSCTPPacks.name: cSctpStatRecSCTPPacks
cSctpStatRecSCTPPacks.description: Number of SCTP packets received from the peers.

cSctpAssocTable.name: cSctpAssocTable
cSctpAssocTable.description: A table containing SCTP association-specific information.

cSctpAssocEntry.name: cSctpAssocEntry
cSctpAssocEntry.description: General common variables and statistics for the whole association.

cSctpAssocId.name: cSctpAssocId
cSctpAssocId.description: Association Identification. Value identifying the association (typically the Initiate Verification Tag). If the selected AssocID is the Initiate Verification Tag, this value must not be zero.

cSctpAssocRemHostName.name: cSctpAssocRemHostName
cSctpAssocRemHostName.description: Peer's DNS name. If no DNS domain name was received at init time (embedded in the INIT or INIT-ACK chunk) from the peer, this entry will be meaningless, therefore it will contain a NULL value. Otherwise, the remote host name received at init time will be stored.

cSctpAssocLocalSCTPPort.name: cSctpAssocLocalSCTPPort
cSctpAssocLocalSCTPPort.description: Local SCTP port number used for this association.

cSctpAssocRemSCTPPort.name: cSctpAssocRemSCTPPort
cSctpAssocRemSCTPPort.description: Remote SCTP port number used for this association.

cSctpAssocRemPrimaryAddressType.name: cSctpAssocRemPrimaryAddressType
cSctpAssocRemPrimaryAddressType.description: Internet type of primary destination IP address. - unknown (0) An unknown address type. This value MUST be used if the value of the corresponding InetAddress object is a zero-length string. It may also be used to indicate an IP address different from IPv4 or IPv6. This value is used in this MIB for error conditions. - ipv4 (1): An IPv4 address as defined by the InetAddressIPv4 textual convention [RFC2851]. - ipv6 (2): An IPv6 address as defined by the InetAddressIPv6 textual convention [RFC2851] This value will be filled in after INIT or INIT ACK messages have been received (when the primary path is selected by SCTP).

cSctpAssocRemPrimaryAddress.name: cSctpAssocRemPrimaryAddress
cSctpAssocRemPrimaryAddress.description: Primary destination IP address. An InetAddress value is always interpreted within the context of an InetAddressType value. This value will be filled in after INIT or INIT ACK messages have been received (when the primary path is selected by SCTP).

cSctpAssocHeartBeatTimer.name: cSctpAssocHeartBeatTimer
cSctpAssocHeartBeatTimer.description: The current heartbeat time-out. The recommended default value is 30000 milliseconds.

cSctpAssocState.name: cSctpAssocState
cSctpAssocState.description: The state of this SCTP association. As in TCP, the only value which may be set by a management station is deleteTCB. Accordingly, it is appropriate for an agent to return a 'badValue' response if a management station attempts to set this object to any other value. If a management station sets this object to the value deleteTCB(9), then this has the effect of deleting the TCB (as defined in SCTP) of the corresponding association on the managed node, resulting in immediate termination of the association. As an implementation-specific option, an ABORT chunk may be sent from the managed node to the other SCTP endpoint.

cSctpAssocInStreams.name: cSctpAssocInStreams
cSctpAssocInStreams.description: Inbound Streams according to the negotiation at association start up. This parameter has to be read-only by the manager.

cSctpAssocOutStreams.name: cSctpAssocOutStreams
cSctpAssocOutStreams.description: Outbound Streams according to the negotiation at association start up. This parameter has to be read-only by the manager.

cSctpAssocMaxRetr.name: cSctpAssocMaxRetr
cSctpAssocMaxRetr.description: The maximum number of data retransmissions in the association context. This value is specific for each association and the upper layer can change it calling the appropriate primitives. This value has to be smaller than the addition of all the maximum number for all the paths (cSctpAssocRemAddressMaxPathRetrans). Recommended value: 10 attempts.

cSctpAssocT1expireds.name: cSctpAssocT1expireds
cSctpAssocT1expireds.description: Number of times that T1 timer expired (timer for sending either INIT or COOKIE-ECHO chunks and receiving an acknowledgment).

cSctpAssocT2expireds.name: cSctpAssocT2expireds
cSctpAssocT2expireds.description: Number of times that T2-shutdown timer expired (shutdown timer).

cSctpAssocRtxChunks.name: cSctpAssocRtxChunks
cSctpAssocRtxChunks.description: Number of data chunks retransmitted to the peer in the current association.

cSctpAssocStartTime.name: cSctpAssocStartTime
cSctpAssocStartTime.description: The value of SysUpTime at the time that this row was created.

cSctpAssocLocalAddressTable.name: cSctpAssocLocalAddressTable
cSctpAssocLocalAddressTable.description: Expanded table of cSctpAssocTable based on the AssocId index. It shows several interesting data for each local address which takes part in this association.

cSctpAssocLocalAddressEntry.name: cSctpAssocLocalAddressEntry
cSctpAssocLocalAddressEntry.description: Local information about the available addresses.

cSctpAssocLocalAddressIPType.name: cSctpAssocLocalAddressIPType
cSctpAssocLocalAddressIPType.description: Internet type of local IP address used for this association. - unknown (0) An unknown address type. This value MUST be used if the value of the corresponding InetAddress object is a zero-length string. It may also be used to indicate an IP address different from IPv4 or IPv6. This value is used in this MIB for error conditions. - ipv4 (1): An IPv4 address as defined by the InetAddressIPv4 textual convention [RFC2851]. - ipv6 (2): An IPv6 address as defined by the InetAddressIPv6 textual convention [RFC2851].

cSctpAssocLocalAddressIP.name: cSctpAssocLocalAddressIP
cSctpAssocLocalAddressIP.description: The value of a local IP address available for this association. An InetAddress value is always interpreted within the context of an InetAddressType value. If SCTP are using DNS names, the mapping to IP address-es will be done at reception of INIT or INIT_ACK messages.

cSctpAssocLocalAddressStartTime.name: cSctpAssocLocalAddressStartTime
cSctpAssocLocalAddressStartTime.description: The value of SysUpTime at the time that this row was created.

cSctpAssocRemAddressTable.name: cSctpAssocRemAddressTable
cSctpAssocRemAddressTable.description: Expanded table of cSctpAssocTable based on the AssocId index. It shows several interesting data for each remote peer IP address which is used in this association.

cSctpAssocRemAddressEntry.name: cSctpAssocRemAddressEntry
cSctpAssocRemAddressEntry.description: Information about THE most important variables for every remote IP address

cSctpAssocRemAddressIPType.name: cSctpAssocRemAddressIPType
cSctpAssocRemAddressIPType.description: Internet type of a remote IP address available for this association. - unknown (0) An unknown address type. This value MUST be used if the value of the corresponding InetAddress object is a zero-length string. It may also be used to indicate an IP address different from IPv4 or IPv6. This value is used in this MIB for error conditions. - ipv4 (1): An IPv4 address as defined by the InetAddressIPv4 textual convention [RFC2851]. - ipv6 (2): An IPv6 address as defined by the InetAddressIPv6 textual convention [RFC2851].

cSctpAssocRemAddressIP.name: cSctpAssocRemAddressIP
cSctpAssocRemAddressIP.description: The value of a remote IP address available for this association. An InetAddress value is always interpreted within the context of an InetAddressType value.

cSctpAssocRemAddressStatus.name: cSctpAssocRemAddressStatus
cSctpAssocRemAddressStatus.description: The current status of the remote transport address, according to [SCTP]. Active means that the threshold of no answer received from this IP address has not been reached. Inactive means that either no heartbeat was received from this address, or any other message, reaching the threshold defined by the protocol.

cSctpAssocRemAddressHBFlag.name: cSctpAssocRemAddressHBFlag
cSctpAssocRemAddressHBFlag.description: The optional Heartbeat associated to one destination transport address could be active or not (value equal to 0 or 1, respectively). An active destination transport address is the one considered available by a peer endpoint for receiving SCTP packets, as it is described in [cSctp].

cSctpAssocRemAddressRTO.name: cSctpAssocRemAddressRTO
cSctpAssocRemAddressRTO.description: The current Retransmission Timeout. T3-rtx timer as defined in the protocol SCTP.

cSctpAssocRemAddressMaxPathRtx.name: cSctpAssocRemAddressMaxPathRtx
cSctpAssocRemAddressMaxPathRtx.description: Maximum number of DATA retransmissions allowed to a remote IP address before it is considered inactive, as defined in [cSctp]. Recommended value 5 attempts.

cSctpAssocRemAddressRtx.name: cSctpAssocRemAddressRtx
cSctpAssocRemAddressRtx.description: Number of DATA retransmissions as defined in [cSctp].

cSctpAssocRemAddressStartTime.name: cSctpAssocRemAddressStartTime
cSctpAssocRemAddressStartTime.description: The value of SysUpTime at the time that this row was created.

cSctpLookupLocalPortTable.name: cSctpLookupLocalPortTable
cSctpLookupLocalPortTable.description: With the use of this table, a list of associations which use that local port can be got

cSctpLookupLocalPortEntry.name: cSctpLookupLocalPortEntry
cSctpLookupLocalPortEntry.description: This table is indexed by local port and association ID. Specifying a local port, we would get a list of the associations whose local port is the one specified

cSctpLookupLocalPortStartTime.name: cSctpLookupLocalPortStartTime
cSctpLookupLocalPortStartTime.description: The value of SysUpTime at the time that this row was created.

cSctpLookupRemPortTable.name: cSctpLookupRemPortTable
cSctpLookupRemPortTable.description: With the use of this table, a list of associations which use that remote port can be got

cSctpLookupRemPortEntry.name: cSctpLookupRemPortEntry
cSctpLookupRemPortEntry.description: This table is indexed by remote port and association ID. Specifying a remote port we would get a list of the associations whose local port is the one specified

cSctpLookupRemPortStartTime.name: cSctpLookupRemPortStartTime
cSctpLookupRemPortStartTime.description: The value of SysUpTime at the time that this row was created.

cSctpLookupRemHostNameTable.name: cSctpLookupRemHostNameTable
cSctpLookupRemHostNameTable.description: With the use of this table, a list of associations with that particular host can be got

cSctpLookupRemHostNameEntry.name: cSctpLookupRemHostNameEntry
cSctpLookupRemHostNameEntry.description: This table is indexed by remote host name and association ID. Specifying a host name we would get a list of the associations specifying that host name as the remote one

cSctpLookupRemHostNameStartTime.name: cSctpLookupRemHostNameStartTime
cSctpLookupRemHostNameStartTime.description: The value of SysUpTime at the time that this row was created.

cSctpLookupRemPrimIPAddrTable.name: cSctpLookupRemPrimIPAddrTable
cSctpLookupRemPrimIPAddrTable.description: With the use of this table, it can be got a list of associations that have that the specified IP address as primary within the remote set of active addresses

cSctpLookupRemPrimIPAddrEntry.name: cSctpLookupRemPrimIPAddrEntry
cSctpLookupRemPrimIPAddrEntry.description: This table is indexed by primary address and association ID. Specifying a primary address, we would get a list of the associations that have the specified remote IP address marked as primary.

cSctpLookupRemPrimIPAddrStartTime.name: cSctpLookupRemPrimIPAddrStartTime
cSctpLookupRemPrimIPAddrStartTime.description: The value of SysUpTime at the time that this row was created.

cSctpLookupRemIPAddrTable.name: cSctpLookupRemIPAddrTable
cSctpLookupRemIPAddrTable.description: With the use of this table, a list of associations that have the specified IP address as one of the remote ones can be got.

cSctpLookupRemIPAddrEntry.name: cSctpLookupRemIPAddrEntry
cSctpLookupRemIPAddrEntry.description: This table is indexed by a remote IP address and association ID. Specifying an IP address we would get a list of the associations that have the specified IP address included within the set of remote IP addresses

cSctpLookupRemIPAddrStartTime.name: cSctpLookupRemIPAddrStartTime
cSctpLookupRemIPAddrStartTime.description: The value of SysUpTime at the time that this row was created.

cSctpGeneralVariablesGroup.name: cSctpGeneralVariablesGroup
cSctpGeneralVariablesGroup.description: Common parameters for all the associations. They can usually be referred as configuration parameters

cSctpStateStatGroup.name: cSctpStateStatGroup
cSctpStateStatGroup.description: The cSctp group of objects to control state changes in the SCTP protocol local layer. They include the data for all the associations.

cSctpOtherStatGroup.name: cSctpOtherStatGroup
cSctpOtherStatGroup.description: The cSctp group of objects providing for management of SCTP most common statistics for the local SCTP layer.

cSctpAssocTablesVariablesGroup.name: cSctpAssocTablesVariablesGroup
cSctpAssocTablesVariablesGroup.description: The sctp group of objects to manage specific local and remote SCTP variables (local and remote tables). These variables include all the SCTP basic features.

cSctpAssocStatGroup.name: cSctpAssocStatGroup
cSctpAssocStatGroup.description: The cSctp group of objects to manage SCTP statistics related to the remote endpoint.

cSctpInverseGroup.name: cSctpInverseGroup
cSctpInverseGroup.description: Objects used in the inverse lookup table.

cSctpCompliance.name: cSctpCompliance
cSctpCompliance.description: The compliance statement for SNMPv3 entities which implement SCTP. As a remark, the not-accessible objects: cSctpAssocLocalAddressIPType and cSctpAssocRemAddressIPType do not support the dns(4)type since the use of the host names is limited to first stage, when the association is being established. cSctpAssocLocalAddressIP and cSctpAssocRemAddressIP will only accept the size of 4 or 16 because it is only required to support IPv4 and unique IPv6 addresses.
